race.comment: TINKER DOT (2) rocketed out of the boxes with a strong early sectional but gathered in and finished in the minors when third (22.28) at this track over 390m. One of the leading chances. JAMES'S ENTITY (1) found some support last start but struggled into fourth (23.12), beaten 4.5 lengths. Was in the money the start prior. Goes well out of this box with a win and three minor placings. Expected to run well. ASTON WARRIOR (3) turned in a plain performance last time when seventh at this track over 390m behind Doongalla Al (23.03) in a Grade 5. Should play a prominent role. JABBERWOCKY (5) scored last time and appeals as a top-three prospect.
